  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexRabbit
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: rabbit
  commonName: Eastern Cottontail
  scientificName: Sylvilagus floridanus
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 9c1cc2802ceb63c499f4d7adef7d5851, type: 3}
  category: Mammal
  habitat: Brush & Forest Edge
  height: 35 - 48 cm
  weight: 1.1 - 1.8 kg
  diet: Herbivore
  rarity: Very common
  shortDescription: A small, agile wild rabbit easily recognized by its fluffy, cotton-like
    white tail.
  behaviorNotes: Often freezes completely motionless to blend into the surroundings.
    If spotted, it flees in a series of sharp zigzag leaps.
  observationTips: Scan ground level near low, dense bushes or tall grass patches
    where they like to hide.
  funFact: To evade predators, cottontails can run in a zigzag pattern at speeds
    of up to 48 km/h.
  facts:
  - To prevent their scent from attracting predators to their young, mothers only
    visit the nest to nurse twice a day.
  - Their long ears can rotate completely independently, allowing them to listen
    for threats from two different directions at once.
  - Their eyes are positioned on the sides of their head, providing a nearly 360-degree
    field of view with only a tiny blind spot.
